==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tarantella
<hw>Tar`an*tel"la</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[It.]</ety>
<fld>(Mus.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A rapid and delirious sort of
Neapolitan dance in 6-8 time, which moves in whirling triplets; -- so
called from a popular notion of its being a remedy against the poisonous
bite of the <xex>tarantula</xex>. Some derive its name from Taranto in
Apulia.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>Music suited to such a dance.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tarantism</ent>⟦br⟧
